recordings.file-name: XC578418-call from a 3CY Mediterranean Gull Cork Lough 21st July 2020_HH_1.mp3
recordings.rmk:
A single call from a 3CY Mediterranean Gull among a throng of feeding Black-headed Gulls, attracted by people feeding the wildfowl there. Unfortunately, it was outnumbered and recording it alone, without interference from the commoner Black-headeds was impossible. This is perhaps my clearest recording of a call from the bird, which wasn't very vocal to begin with. 

I put 'adult' down in the fields above, because the bird wasn't  a juvenile, or a hatchling, and nor was the age unknown. Also, the calls seem the same as those given by adults, and it is in the process of moulting into an 'adult winter' plumage, but, strictly speaking, it still had many retained outer second generation primaries.
